OL,3,CFailings found in care of man who
OL,4,Ckilled his father after escaping from
OL,5,Chospital
OL,7,F"Throughout the inquest, staff have
OL,8,Fsought to give the impression that it
OL,9,Fwas Dan's fault for not engaging with
OL,10,Fmental health services, leading to a
OL,11,Frecurrence of his psychosis and the
OL,12,Ftragic events that unfolded.
OL,14,F"The professionals giving evidence
OL,15,Fappear blind to their failure to reach
OL,16,Fout and engage with him. It was their
OL,17,Fduty to care for him.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/13
